observations.recommendation:
1. For the Municipal Assessor to prepare annually the updated Assessment Roll and provide the same to the Municipal Treasurer as basis for collection of real property and special education tax;
2. For the Municipal Treasurer to set-up and update the Real Property Tax Account Register (RPTAR)/ Taxpayer’s index based on the submitted Assessment Roll and furnish the Accounting Office of the duly certified list of taxpayers, the amount due and collectible for the year. Henceforth, such list shall be provided at the beginning of each year;
3. For the Municipal Accountant to set-up the Real Property Tax and Special Education Tax (RPT/SET) receivable as soon as the MTO will submit the duly certified list and book all the necessary entries affecting the receivables and deferred income accounts.

